11. Current security hardening pass in progress

- Hardened `services/ingress_api.py`:
- request body size limit
- maximum `external_ref` and `external_leaf_ref` lengths
- maximum batch size
- maximum canonicalized material size
- Antelope account-name validation for `submitter`
- rejection of `null` payloads
- default response redaction for `canonical_form`, `manifest`, and other raw debug material
- opt-in raw debug output via `include_debug_material=true`

- Hardened `services/finality_watcher.py`:
- request body size limit
- strict `request_id` validation as 64-char hex
- strict `tx_id` validation as 64-char hex
- bounded `trace_id` validation
- Antelope account-name validation for `submitter` and `contract`
- stricter anchor metadata validation for hashes and IDs
- idempotent register behavior for identical requests
- conflict rejection for reused `request_id` with different immutable fields
- conflict rejection for rewriting `tx_id`, `block_num`, `commitment_id`, or `batch_id`
- prevention of status regression from `finalized` back to `included`

- Added hardening documentation:
- `docs/denotary-security-hardening.md`

- Updated related docs:
- `README.md`
- `docs/denotary-ingress-api.md`
- `docs/denotary-finality-services.md`
- `docs/denotary-l1-test-matrix.md`
- `docs/denotary-l1-development-plan.md`
- `docs/denotary-l1-backlog.md`

